<div id="body-wrap">
  <div id="headings">
    <h1>
      Realistic Virtual Human Rendering in Real-Time
    </h1>
    A perceptual study on a virtual human model.
  </div>

  <form action="/submit" method="post">

    <div id="section-one">
      <h2>
        Part 1 of 4: Meet Tatiana — she's a virtual human rendered in Unreal Engine 4. 
      </h2>
      
      <h4>
        In this survey, you will be asked to rate Tatiana's photorealism 
        in different rendering qualities. Each rendered image is labelled based
        on quality. To begin, we will start with this scale:
      </h4>

      <p class="description">
        Scale: <br>
        <b>1 • FAKE</b> = This image is of a poor-quality generated virtual human <br>
        <b>7 • PHOTOREALISTIC</b> = I cannot distinguish this image from a photograph of a real person
      </p>

      {{#each sectionOne}}
      <div class="question">
        <div class="img-slider-container">
          <img src="{{this.link}}">

          <div class="label-left">
            Quality A
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="options">
          <h3>{{this.label}} <br> In this image, does she look fake or photorealistic?</h3>

          <div class="answer-wrap">
            <div class="label-wrap" style="text-align: right;">
              FAKE
            </div>

            <div class="radio-wrap">
              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="1">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">1</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="2">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">2</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="3">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">3</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="4">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">4</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="5">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">5</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="6">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">6</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="7">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">7</label>
              </span>

            </div>

            <div class="label-wrap" style="text-align: left;">
              PHOTOREALISTIC
            </div>

          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
      {{/each}}

      <div style="text-align: center;">
        <span class="next-btn" onclick="goSection2()">Next</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="section-two" hidden>
      <h2>
        Part 2 of 4: This is Tatiana with (previous) Quality A next to (new) Quality B —
        we will see if Quality B affects your prerception of her realism.
      </h2>
      <p class="description">
        Scale: <br>
        <b>1 • LESS REALISTC</b> = Quality B is less photorealistic than Quality A<br>
        <b>4 • NO DIFFERENCE</b> = Quality B is same level of photorealism with Quality A<br>
        <b>7 • MORE REALISTIC</b> = Quality B is more photorealistic than Quality A
        <br><br>
        Move the circle slider to either left or right to fully view each quality.
      </p>

      {{#each sectionTwo}}
      <div class="question-slider">
        <div class="img-slider-container">

          <div class="img-comp">
            <img src="{{this.linkA}}">

            <div class="label-right">
              Quality B
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="img-comp img-comp-top">
            <div class="label-left">
              Quality A
            </div>

            <img src="{{this.linkB}}">

          </div>

        </div>

        <div class="options">
          <h3>{{this.label}} <br> Is Quality B: less realistic, the same or more realistic?</h3>

          <div class="answer-wrap">
            <div class="label-wrap" style="text-align: right;">
              LESS REALISTC
            </div>

            <div class="radio-wrap">
              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="1">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">1</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="2">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">2</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="3">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">3</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="4" checked>
                <label for="{{this.name}}">4</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="5">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">5</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="6">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">6</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="7">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">7</label>
              </span>
            </div>

            <div class="label-wrap" style="text-align: left;">
              MORE REALISTC
            </div>

          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
      {{/each}}

      <div style="text-align: center;">
        <span class="next-btn" onclick="goSection3()">Next</span>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div id="section-three" hidden>
      <h2>
        Part 3 of 4: Compare (previous) Quality B to (new) Quality C 
        — does Quality C affect your prerception of her realism?
      </h2>
      <p class="description">
        Scale: <br>
        <b>1 • LESS REALISTC</b> = Quality C is less photorealistic than Quality B<br>
        <b>4 • NO DIFFERENCE</b> = Quality C is same level of photorealism with Quality B<br>
        <b>7 • MORE REALISTIC</b> = Quality C is more photorealistic than Quality B
        <br><br>
        Move the circle slider to either left or right to fully view each quality.
      </p>

      {{#each sectionThree}}
      <div class="question-slider">
        <div class="img-slider-container">

          <div class="img-comp">
            <img src="{{this.linkA}}">

            <div class="label-right">
              Quality C
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="img-comp img-comp-top">
            <div class="label-left">
              Quality B
            </div>

            <img src="{{this.linkB}}">

          </div>

        </div>

        <div class="options">
          <h3>{{this.label}} <br> Is Quality C: less realistic, the same or more realistic?</h3>

          <div class="answer-wrap">
            <div class="label-wrap" style="text-align: right;">
              LESS REALISTC
            </div>

            <div class="radio-wrap">
              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="1">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">1</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="2">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">2</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="3">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">3</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="4" checked>
                <label for="{{this.name}}">4</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="5">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">5</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="6">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">6</label>
              </span>

              <span class="radio-line">
                <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="7">
                <label for="{{this.name}}">7</label>
              </span>
            </div>

            <div class="label-wrap" style="text-align: left;">
              MORE REALISTC
            </div>

          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
      {{/each}}

      <div style="text-align: center;">
        <span class="next-btn" onclick="goSection4()">Next</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="section-four" hidden>
      <h2>
        Part 4 of 4: Let's look at the details — which image looks more realistic?
      </h2>

      {{#each sectionFour}}
      <div class="question-slider">

        <div class="img-slider-container">

          <div class="img-comp">
            <img src="{{this.linkA}}">

            <div class="label-right">
              Image A
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="img-comp img-comp-top">
            <div class="label-left">
              Image B
            </div>

            <img src="{{this.linkB}}">

          </div>

        </div>

        <div class="options">
          <h3>{{this.label}} <br> Which image looks more realistic?</h3>

          <div class="answer-wrap">
            <div class="label-wrap" style="text-align: right;">
              A
            </div>

            <div class="radio-wrap">
              <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="1">
              <span></span>
              <input type="radio" id="age1" name="{{this.name}}" value="2">
            </div>

            <div class="label-wrap" style="text-align: left;">
              B
            </div>

          </div>

        </div>

      </div>
      {{/each}}

      <div style="text-align: center;">
        <button>Submit</button>
      </div>
    </div>


  </form>

  <div style="height: 40px"> </div>

</div>